General interval comment: Fragment of 1 large clast with attached clastic and welded (?) matrix;
Clast comments: clast types: 1) two clasts of this type: very large pebble and granule sized clast of moderately vesicular, black and euhedral plag phyric dacite (similar to commonly present dacite); 2) lithic fragment of probably altered volcanic, moderately vesicular, granule sized
Matrix comments: Glassy matrix with vesicles probably consists of welded ash and contains several <2mm large plagioclase crystals (5-10 vol.%) and subordinate lithic fragments (prob alt. volcanics).

General interval comment: artificial grading from medium to coarse ash.
Matrix comments: components: 1) black vitric fragments of probably dacite lava, angular 2) crystals, mostly plagioclase, angular 3) lithics, altered volcaniclastics, subangular, different colors
